{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17608229","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17608229"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:30:36+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:30:36+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15993"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15993","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15993"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.09,0,0.03,0.03,0.85]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8684"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63446"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8684","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8684"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15993"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48899"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"3618"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"8576"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20783"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20785"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63446","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/63446"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring early embryonic development, the embryo must establish connections with the developing placenta to ensure proper nutrition and waste removal.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary function of the connecting stalk during embryological development?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Develops into the primitive streak","Generates the chorion frondosum","Creates the yolk sac","Forms the amniotic cavity","Contains blood vessels connecting embryo to placenta"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Econnecting stalk contains blood vessels connecting the embryo to placenta\u003C/strong\u003E and eventually develops into the umbilical cord. It forms from extraembryonic mesoderm during the third week of development and houses the umbilical vessels that are crucial for embryonic nutrition and waste removal.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E    \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eamniotic cavity\u003C/strong\u003E forms from the epiblast cells that create a space above the embryonic disc\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eprimitive streak\u003C/strong\u003E is the site of gastrulation where the three germ layers form\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eyolk sac\u003C/strong\u003E is formed from extraembryonic endoderm and provides nutrients early in development\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Echorion frondosum\u003C/strong\u003E is the embryonic portion of the placenta that develops from trophoblast tissue\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The connecting stalk forms the umbilical cord and contains vital blood vessels connecting the embryo to the placenta.","The connecting stalk develops from extraembryonic mesoderm and forms during the third week of development."],"references":["Gaillard R, Steegers EA, de Jongste JC, Hofman A, Jaddoe VW. Tracking of fetal growth characteristics during different trimesters and the risks of adverse birth outcomes. Int J Epidemiol. 2014 Aug;43(4):1140-53. doi: 10.1093/ije/dyu036. Epub 2014 Mar 5. PMID: 24603318; PMCID: PMC4258770","Chen X, Liu H, Li Y, Zhang W, Zhou A, Xia W, Xu S. First-trimester fetal size, accelerated growth in utero, and child neurodevelopment in a cohort study. BMC Med. 2024 Apr 29;22(1):181. doi: 10.1186/s12916-024-03390-3. PMID: 38685041; PMCID: PMC11059611","Godfrey KM, Inskip HM, Hanson MA. The long-term effects of prenatal development on growth and metabolism. Semin Reprod Med. 2011 May;29(3):257-65. doi: 10.1055/s-0031-1275518. Epub 2011 Jul 18. PMID: 21769765; PMCID: PMC3685133","Singh, V. (2022). Textbook of clinical embryology, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48899"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15993"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48899","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/48899"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-20T22:51:41+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-20T22:52:15+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8684"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63446"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying an